        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> I have tried using call of bones lately and am not liking what I am seeing. When I used allure of death I could go from oom to FM and lose about 2 bubs of life. The other day I was at 100% life, 60% mana. I used call of bones and by the time I was FM I was at just under 60% life. I haven't timed it to see how much faster I regen with call, than with allure. But as is I am thinking that having enough HP left to be able to pull is worth the extra time it takes to get FM. I generally do not like pulling if I am below 50% life when I solo. Anyways I have 526HP unbuffed, and about 1282 mana. Does anyone know how much HP I need with my current mana total to be able to go from oom to fm with call without losing more than 60% of my life? Or what ratio of HP/Mana I would need?</P><P>I would also really like to find some +HP gear. Are there anyplaces that I could camp solo or with a small group at level 34 to get any decent +HP gear? Preferably with +int, or +mana as well.</P><P><BR><a target="new"  href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=117251">Talanor S`Tox</a><BR>Necromancer of Innoruuk</P><P><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=116028">Tazuuk</a><BR>Necromancer of Cazic Thule<BR></font></td>

