        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         As you go up in the lich line, you are going to lose health faster and faster.  You are going to gain mana faster, too.  Just the way it works.  Keep allure if you want to be efficient while medding.  Use CoB if you want to scare noobs or if you need mana fast.  Like, if you were in the middle of a battle.  The later lich spells are nice but they are not without their downsides.</P><P>At that level, I don't know.  At later levels, health is clearly the way to go.  In mid levels, I guess it's a tossup.  Would you rather have more health?  Is your mana takeing you as far as you need to go?  Or are you finding that your mana pool is a bit on the short side for your game play?  It's all up to you.</P><P><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26159">Reegor</A> Mortees<BR>scaled Warlock<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
