         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>At that level, I don't know.  At later levels, health is clearly the way to go.  In mid levels, I guess it's a tossup.  Would you rather have more health?  Is your mana takeing you as far as you need to go?  Or are you finding that your mana pool is a bit on the short side for your game play?  It's all up to you.</P><P>&lt;A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26159"&gt;Reegor&lt;/A&gt; Mortees<BR>scaled Warlock<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Currently when I solo a dark blue mob(for instance a snow cougar, or one of the guards at the toll booth) I use about 50%-80% of my mana depending on resists. That is using dooming darkness, invoke fear, Vampiric Curse, VoS, and Boil Blood. My last 3 spell slots are taken up with allure/call, HS, and FD. The reason I do not like being below 50% though is that if fear breaks on toll booth guards they drop me pretty fast.</P><P><BR><a target="new"  href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=117251">Talanor S`Tox</a><BR>Necromancer of Innoruuk</P><P><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=116028">Tazuuk</a><BR>Necromancer of Cazic Thule<BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
