        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Mana generation is a corner stone for a necromancer. You definately want to take advantage of COB and the other spells in our lich line as soon as you are able. </P><P>Just think of it this way, lets say you are killing 4 critters every 12 minutes, and each critter is taking 500 mana to kill. Regardless whether your mana pool is 1200 or 2000, you will still have to generate 16 mana a tick to keep up. If you cannot generate that, you are going to fall behind. </P><P>At the end of the day who is going to be further ahead, the guy with an extra 500 points of mana on their total, or the one who generates an extra 5 mana a tick? I know which guy I would rather be.</P><P>But, I remember my first few times in COB, and I was like "holy shit, my HP bar is dropping like a stone". All I can say, is you get used to it, and as you build in more HP items, it becomes more and more managable. Gear upgrades really start to happen at level 35 to 40, as you start to have access to some better dungeons.</P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black<BR>Warlock - Terris Thule</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

